hopobject.body: Withdraw cash medical-x.com "Usually prices follow transactions, so if transactions remained as depressed as they have been, a 10 to 20 percent correction in some segments of the market cannot be ruled out, especially in the top end of the market," he said, noting that this decline would take place over the next one to two years. Hong Kong has seen an unprecedented rise in residential property prices in the recent years, soaring 120 percent since 2008, supported by record low interest rates and demand across the border in China. Given its sky-high property prices, the city is ranked as the 10th most expensive city for expatriates in Asia, according to expatriate management firm ECA International.
